sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Admin
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Controller Manager<br/>Service Account Token
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant API as Model Registry REST API<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP TLS1.2+

    %% Flow 1: ModelRegistry CR Creation
    Note over User,DB: Flow 1: ModelRegistry CR Creation

    User->>K8s: POST ModelRegistry CR<br/>kubectl/oc credentials
    K8s->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate Request<br/>K8s API Server cert
    Webhook->>K8s: Validation Response<br/>Service Account Token
    K8s->>Controller: Watch Notification<br/>Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8s: Create Resources<br/>(Deployment, Service, Route, RBAC)<br/>Service Account Token
    Controller->>DB: Optionally provision PostgreSQL<br/>Password from Secret

    %% Flow 2: Model Registry API Request (OAuth Secured)
    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Model Registry API Request (OAuth Secured)

    User->>Router: GET/POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/*<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
    Router->>OAuth: Forward Request<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+
    OAuth->>OAuthServer: Validate Bearer Token<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+
    OAuthServer-->>OAuth: Token Valid
    OAuth->>API: Forward Request<br/>HTTP (Validated Token in header)
    API->>DB: Query/Update Metadata<br/>PostgreSQL/MySQL Protocol<br/>Password/Client Cert
    DB-->>API: Query Result
    API-->>OAuth: JSON Response
    OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    %% Flow 3: Database Initialization
    Note over User,DB: Flow 3: Database Connection Initialization

    API->>DB: Connect to Database<br/>5432/3306 TCP TLS1.2+ (optional)<br/>Password from Secret
    API->>DB: CREATE DATABASE (if enabled)<br/>SQL over TLS
    API->>DB: Run Schema Migrations<br/>SQL over TLS
    DB-->>API: Schema Ready

    %% Flow 4: Operator Metrics Collection
    Note over User,DB: Flow 4: Operator Metrics Collection

    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>Service Account Token
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Mgr as Controller Manager Metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    Prom->>RBACProxy: GET /metrics<br/>Service Account Token
    RBACProxy->>K8s: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS TLS1.3
    K8s-->>RBACProxy: Authorized
    RBACProxy->>Mgr: Forward Request<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+
    Mgr-->>RBACProxy: Prometheus Metrics
    RBACProxy-->>Prom: Metrics Response
